        <abstract> 
<p>Has studied CD’s Jamaican hive-bees and finds them identical to <hi rend="italic">Apis mellifica</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Discusses the structure of wasps’ and bees’ nests</p>
            <p>and the occurrence of winged and apterous individuals within some insect genera and species.</p>
